<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5635] ThriftServer.stop() hangs forever</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5635</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve written a very small main() method just to start to test &quot;how to embed Cassandra&quot;. But the code hangs while executing CassandraDaemon.stop()...&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve used a default &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.yaml&lt;/tt&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cassandraDaemon = new CassandraDaemon();
cassandraDaemon.init(null);
cassandraDaemon.start();
cassandraDaemon.stop();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;CassandraDaemon.stop()&lt;/tt&gt; calls &lt;tt&gt;ThriftServer.stop()}, which ends somehow in {{TCustomServerSocket.close()&lt;/tt&gt;, which sets its field &lt;tt&gt;serverSocket=null&lt;/tt&gt;. This causes &lt;tt&gt;CustomTThreadPoolServer.server()&lt;/tt&gt; to loop forever, because it&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;stopped&lt;/tt&gt; field is still &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; - &lt;tt&gt;TServerTransport.accept()&lt;/tt&gt; immediatly throws a &lt;tt&gt;TTransportException&lt;/tt&gt; because &lt;tt&gt;TCustomServerSocket&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;serverSocket&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
