                            <comment id="13982494" author="dbrosius" created="Sun, 27 Apr 2014 22:28:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On trunk at least, what&apos;s keeping it alive is the threads&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;COMMIT-LOG-ALLOCATOR  (CommitLogSegmentManager.java)&lt;br/&gt;
PERIODIC-COMMIT-LOG-SYNCER (PeriodicCommitLogService.java)&lt;br/&gt;
ACCEPT-(ip) (MessagingService)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;not of which are terminated by CassandraDaemon.stop()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;might need a StorageService.instance.drain(); afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13994755" author="dbrosius" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 02:31:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;make SlabPoolCleaner thread, a daemon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
